In case you missed it, here are the top Sport stories of the week: 1. BREAKING: ROYAL AM RELEASE SEVEN PLAYERS Royal AM have released seven players to trim their squad to a manageable size in a bid to maintain their positive start in the DStv Premiership. 2. EX-AMAZULU STAR DIES Former AmaZulu star Sphiwe Naval Mavimbela has sadly passed away. 3. HERE'S HOW IRVIN KHOZA HELPED LUCKY LEKGWATHI Former Orlando Pirates captain, Lucky Lekgwathi, does not doubt that he would be counted among the many former players who blew their fortune and ended up broke if it were not not the guidance and advice of those close to him throughout his career. 4. CAF'S ABOUT TURN! The Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) finals will revert back to being played in June and July next year. 5. CHIPPA RUN RISK OF FIFA BAN Fifa has ordered Chippa United to pay their former striker Augustine Kwem R200 000 and a 5% interest of the amount.